<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-06-28T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-06-28T16:00:00-05:00" n="129" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d129">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01 Manchuria/282: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1" type="to">Johnson</persName>)</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-28T17:00:00-04:00">June 28, 1932—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>179. Your 708, June 24, 8 p.m.<note n="84" xml:id="d129fn84">Not
                                printed.</note></p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>On June 23 the Chinese. Chargé d’Affaires handed to the Secretary
                                a note quoting substantially the same message in regard to Japan’s
                                recognition of the Manchoukuo régime as that quoted in your telegram
                                under reference.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>The Department is acknowledging the Chargé’s note with a brief
                                statement as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>“In reply I desire to inform you that the subject matter of
                                        your note under acknowledgment is being studied in
                                        connection with developments in the situation in Manchuria
                                        which are continuing to receive the attentive consideration
                                        of the American Government.”</p>
                                </quote></item>
                            <label>3.</label>
                            <item>You are authorized to so inform the Ministry of Foreign Affairs in
                                reply to the note quoted in your telegram under reference.</item>
                            <label>4.</label>
                            <item>Inform Tokyo.</item>
                        </list>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_SHL1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>